Just as we repress our pain and that which is dark, we also repress our goodness and our light. 

If you have struggled with dieting and disordered eating concerns, somewhere on your journey, 'all of who you are' wasn't allowed in some way. 

I have heard repeatedly over the years , "I wasn't allowed to feel sad or angry...and...I also wasn't allowed to be too happy, or too big (in energy or body size!). 

Time to let go of the Tall Poppy Sydnrome glass ceiling. All of who you are is allowed here. It is time to let yourself shine.

This might feel scary, it means you might even outgrow the people around you. It means a journey through grief and loss (can't wait to talk about this more with my wonderful colleague @cait_wotherspoon on the Soul Sessions with Jodie Gale podcast later this year!). It feels painful as you let go of old ways of being and step into the unknown. 

There are even books written about how hard this is, The Fear of Freedom for example. 

Go for it. You won't regret it in the long-term.

